# diffusers style

Authoritative source: `AGENTS.md` (= `.ai/AGENTS.md`) → "Coding style" / "Code formatting" ("write code as
simple and explicit as possible"; "`make style` and `make fix-copies` should be run before opening a PR").
Defer to it. The enforcement specifics the pack pins — run before committing:
```bash
make style        # ruff check --fix + ruff format + doc-builder   (mutating)
make quality      # ruff check + ruff format --check + doc-builder + check_doc_toc.py  (check-only)
make fix-copies   # re-sync `# Copied from` + regenerate dummy objects (see diffusers-copied-from)
```
- Linter is **ruff** (not black); line length **119** (`pyproject.toml [tool.ruff]`).
- Apache-2.0 header on every new `.py` (top-level `__init__.py` excepted); **new code prefers** modern
  type hints (`int | None`, `tuple[int, int]`); the codebase still contains `Optional[...]`/`Tuple[...]`
  and this is **not lint-enforced**. Google-style docstrings.
- Never silently break public API — go through `from ...utils import deprecate`.
